{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"49a4f161-3801-421d-a1ed-29f38f664b22","content":"Here's the skip attribute for each framework:\n\n**MSTest**\n```csharp\n[Ignore(\"Reason for skipping\")]\n```\n\n**xUnit**\n```csharp\n[Fact(Skip = \"Reason for skipping\")]\n// or for theories:\n[Theory(Skip = \"Reason for skipping\")]\n```\n\n**NUnit**\n```csharp\n[Ignore(\"Reason for skipping\")]\n```\n\n**TUnit**\n```csharp\n[Skip(\"Reason for skipping\")]\n```\n\nAll four will mark the test as skipped/ignored in test results (not failed, not passed) and display the reason message in the test output.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"814ab157-eee4-4540-8f29-c5108ebba2b7","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about the correct attribute syntax for skipping tests with a reason message in each of the four .NET test frameworks: MSTest, xUnit, NUnit, and TUnit. This is a knowledge question I can answer directly.","outputTokens":223,"requestId":"702A:114A89:B0090F:CC0CEE:69F2AC85"},"id":"9742ca33-39ec-40cc-a68f-86befd96b2fc","timestamp":"2026-04-30T01:12:43.390Z","parentId":"554beb97-9bac-4961-ab76-dc29e3d5678f"}
